![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/c76e00e3-1f8d-498b-b2b3-d3033db6fe6c/received_3654277644829035.jpeg?format=original)

Ian Riccaboni & Caprice Coleman welcomed the audience to the broadcast before transitioning into the opening contest.

*   ## **_ROH Men's World Television Championship Match: Kyle Fletcher (c) vs. Lee Johnson._**
    

ABSOLUTELY INCREDIBLE OPENER! STAR MAKING PERFORMANCES. GO OUT OF YOUR WAY TO SEE THIS.

*   **_WINNER: KYLE FLETCHER RETAINS_**
    

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/486fd08c-7072-4c09-9214-0342fd49e2a6/received_438070908733672.jpeg?format=original)

*   ## **_Mei Seira & EXV (Mina Shirakawa & Maika) vs. Saya Kamitani, Tam Nakano, & AZM._**
    

Second excellent match in a row. Mina Shirakawa is SO OVER but all the girls did a great job here.

*   **_WINNER: MEI SEIRA AND EXV_**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/dc694034-9b00-42e1-8dd5-fa2469718178/Screenshot_20240405_175644.jpg?format=original)

Post match, Mariah May comes out and reunites with her ex…. tag team partner Mina. She teases trouble before hughing Mina and reluctantly allowing Mina's new friends to celebrate with them.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/6379dbbc-3b65-4ffa-b7c6-bc990daff081/processed_20240405_182010.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_ROH World Tag Team Championship Match: The Undisputed Kingdom (Matt Taven & Mike Bennett) (c) vs. The Infantry (Shawn Dean & Carlie Bravo)._**
    

The Undisputed Kingdom retains in a pretty great match with a lame duck ending after Wardlow interference with one clothesline.

*   **_WINNERS: Undisputed Kingdom_**
    

* * *

*   ## **_ROH Women's World Television Championship Tournament - Finals: Billie Starkz vs. Queen Aminata._**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/b05386b8-c313-4a30-be81-f6211a395ca4/received_373314145680417.jpeg?format=original)

These ladies absolutely SMASHED IT. Though the finish of the match saw Billie Starks fake a brutal injury to steal a win and become Women’s TV Champion.

*   **_WINNER AND FIRST EVER WOMEN’S TV CHAMPION: BILLIE STARKZ_**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/84e6340e-0c9d-4122-a107-63ee16d07fc3/received_415029831114899.jpeg?format=original)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5c0e2a90-804b-4004-8909-0fcad595d903/received_1502878440633923.jpeg?format=original)

*   ## **_IMPROMTU 6 MAN TAG TEAM TITLE MATCH: BULLET CLUB GOLD VS LANCE ARCHER, ALEX ZAYNE AND MINORU SUZUKI_**
    

The BCG is out for an open challenge but they will put their belts on the line. Archer comes out with his NJPW partner Alex Zayne and then SURPRISE KA ZE NI NARE!!! Suzuki is here!

*   **_WINNERS: BCG_**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1a643e6d-f67a-4b78-9e2c-4b0eeea57bd9/received_815078377307027.jpeg?format=original)

Post Match, the Acclaimed arrive to chase off BCG

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ba5cf292-f3bd-44bd-86bf-f833ed5811b3/received_949459296898916.jpeg?format=original)

*   ## **_FIGHT WITHOUT HONOR: DALTON CASTLE VS JOHNNY TV_**
    

Dalton Castle arrives flanked by a whole new group of bootlegged boys.

This may have been the WORST Fight Without Honor I’ve ever seen. A pretty paint by numbers house show-esque No DQ match until it devolved into some outrageous shenanigans.

At one point Paul Walter Houser shows up and just sits there. Until he gets involved and hands Dalton a bag of tacks, but NOT before they rub each others faces.

So weird.

*   **_WINNER:DALTON CASTLE_**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a54c8df4-9e6e-4b6b-ba37-e628cef87d3e/received_1097914784756672.jpeg?format=original)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/6d77c4ce-ea9b-4907-975a-32a94140bf86/received_1081623149803621.jpeg?format=original)

*   ## **_ROH Women's World Championship Match: Athena (c) vs. Hikaru Shida_**
    

Shida and Athena easily bring this show back on track with an excellent even back and forth match.

*   **_WINNER: ATHENA RETAINS FOR THE 50TH TIME_**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/8c2f165d-bb3c-4777-b8f6-2ea0b21c09c0/received_3754610481425789.jpeg?format=original)

